WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.000
A game can already move beautifully and still feel unfinished in silence.
FRAMEFOLEY turns one short clip into a tested, inspectable sound kit.

00:09.000 --> 00:18.000
It is not a chat box and does not pretend to understand the whole game.
It helps a creator make three precise sound decisions.

00:18.000 --> 00:28.000
JELLY RELAY is an original twelve-second demo generated from code,
with no third-party footage and no embedded audio.

00:28.000 --> 00:40.000
Mark the glass landing, bubble pop, and route confirmation,
then lock one of four bounded sonic styles.

00:40.000 --> 00:52.000
Each event receives exactly two independent candidates.
This run is explicitly CACHED DEMO and MOCKED LOCAL STORAGE.

00:52.000 --> 01:02.000
It never calls cached files live or claims they reached B2.
Final-version LIVE evidence is captured separately.

01:02.000 --> 01:15.000
Genblaze orchestrates each generated candidate and records its provenance.
Backblaze B2 stores source, assets, manifests, QC, derivatives, preview, and export.

01:15.000 --> 01:24.000
Deterministic code performs the technical audio checks.
The developer still makes the creative decision by ear.

01:24.000 --> 01:35.000
FRAMEFOLEY measures duration, peak, RMS, silence, channels,
sample rate, and SHA-256 using fixed deterministic thresholds.

01:35.000 --> 01:47.000
Repair may trim, control gain, limit, downmix, resample, and convert.
Original lineage stays intact; canonical manifests are never edited.

01:47.000 --> 01:58.000
Play A alone, switch to B in exact video context, compare metrics,
and approve by ear. Nothing autoplays.

01:58.000 --> 02:11.000
The authoritative server render delays approved WAVs to exact timestamps,
applies bounded gain, mixes, limits, and encodes H.264/AAC.

02:11.000 --> 02:22.000
The mix map records event, candidate, timestamp, gain,
source hash, and render hash. This recording remains LOCAL / MOCKED.

02:22.000 --> 02:34.000
The deterministic ZIP contains preview, WAV, OGG, waveforms,
QC, manifests, project state, and provenance.

02:34.000 --> 02:44.000
The ZIP receives a size, timestamp, inventory, and SHA-256.
Production B2 uses the same private project object path.

02:44.000 --> 02:53.000
The provenance inspector exposes source label, prompt, parameters,
provider/model, lineage, timestamps, object key, hashes, QC, and approval.

02:53.000 --> 02:56.000
The sound may be synthetic. The history is not.
That is FRAMEFOLEY.
